Fury's Edge</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cydmab>Cydmab</A> at: 1/16/03 10:38:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1207<br> <font color=#333333>(1/21/03 6:55:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=512.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Quick Summoning Noob Question</span><hr size=1> Some have qs3 but I would highly most severly recommend not getting that, QS2 + a summoning haste item is 50% which is max.. Unless for some unknown reason you absolutely terribly cannot live without a 6 second coth or you get like 13 AA a day I would not get 3 .. 9 points is a lot to lower the casting time on a simple utility spell <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
